{title: When The Cactus Is In Bloom}
{artist: Bill Monroe}
{composer: unknown}

[C]The cattle prowled and the coyotes howled
[F]Out on the Great Divide
I [C]never done no wrong just singing a song
[D7]As down the trail I ride
[C]The rattlesnakes rattle at the prairie dogs
[F]Don't you hear that mournful tune
For [C]it's roundup time away out West
When the [G7]cactus are in [C]bloom
Daylight comes and the cowhands yell
[F]They call out every man
I [G7]throw my saddle on my old cow-horse
I drink my coffee from a [C]can
The sun goes down on the cattle trail
[F]I'm gazing at the moon
For [C]it's roundup time away out West
When the [G7]cactus are in [C]bloom
We don't have cold weather
[F]It never snows or rains
That [C]is where the sunshine's best
[D7]Out on the western plains
[C]Some of the boys have gone away
[F]But they will be back soon
For [C]it's roundup time away out West
When the [G7]cactus are in [C]bloom
repeat #3 & 4